lead_paragraph: The Courier Enquirer fears the approaching State election "excites to little interest in the great body. of the Whig party, and says: "Their preparation for the contest does not correspond with its momentous character. This lack of activity springs from no misgiving or doubt respecting the relative merits of the measures at issue but rather from an over confidence in an easy victory.
